						<h5>STEP 3: React at 16 degree for 2-4 hours.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 4: Transfer all of the mixture to 100 ml DH5a competent cell and put it on the ice for 30 minutes.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 5: Incubate the cell at 42 degree for 90 seconds and transfer it on ice immediately.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 6: Add 400 ml LB into the tube and grow in 37 degree shaker for 1 hour.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 7: Spread 200 ml colon on the agar plate with X-gal, IPTG and Ampicillin.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 8: Grow overnight at 37 degree.</h5>
						<h5>STEP 9: Confirm by colony PCR (use primer M13F and M13R).</h5>

